```
- **View Fleet:** Display a list of all vehicles in the fleet with essential details like year, make, model, and VIN.
- **Vehicle Details:** View detailed information about individual vehicles, including images, specifications, and maintenance requirements.
- **Maintenance Tracking:** Keep track of maintenance schedules and requirements for each vehicle.
- **Search and Filter:** Easily search and filter vehicles based on various criteria.
- **Car News:** Displays a list of links to news articles regarding vehicles.
```

card.desc:
## **User Story 1: View Vehicle List**

- As a fleet manager
- I want to view a list of vehicles currently in the fleet
- So that I can quickly see which vehicles are available and their statuses.

### **Acceptance Criteria**

#### **Display Vehicle List**

- Given I am on the homepage of the fleet management app
- When the page loads
- Then I should see a list of all vehicles in the fleet

#### Vehicle Details in List

- Given I am view the “Vehicle List”
- When the vehicle list is displayed
- Then I should see the following details
  - VIN (data-mask all but last 6 characters)
  - Make
  - Model
  - Year
  - Status (e.g., available, in maintenance, in use)
  - Current location

#### Accurate Data Display

- Given there are vehicles in the fleet database
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then the displayed list should accurately reflect the current inventory and statuses of all vehicles in the fleet

#### Empty State Handling

- Given there are no vehicles in the fleet database
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then I should see a message indicating that no vehicles are currently available in the fleet.

#### Search

- Given I am viewing the “Vehicle List”
- When I use the search option
- Then the vehicle list should update to display only the vehicles that match the search criteria.

#### Pagination

- Given there are more vehicles in the fleet than can be displayed on a single page
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then the list should be paginated, and I should be able to navigate between pages
card.name: US-1 Acceptance Criteria: View Vehicle List

card.desc:
## User Story 2: View Vehicle Details

- As a fleet manager
- When I click on a vehicle in the list
- Then I should see its detailed specifications, including make, model, year, and maintenance schedule

### Acceptance Criteria

#### Clickable Vehicle Entries

- Given I am viewing the vehicle list
- When I click on a vehicle entry
- Then I should be navigated to a detailed view page for that vehicle

#### Display Vehicle Specifications

- Given I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- When the page loads
- Then I should see the vehicle’s specifications, including
  - Make
  - Model
  - Year
  - VIN (Vehicle Identification Number)
  - License Plate Number (if applicable)
  - Current Status

#### Display Maintenance Schedule

- Given I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- When the page loads
- Then I should see the vehicles maintenance schedule, including:
  - Upcoming maintenance tasks with due dates
  - Past maintenance history with completion dates
  - Current maintenance status (e.g., overdue, upcoming, completed)

#### Navigation to Maintenance History

- Given I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- When I click on a “View Maintenance History” link or button
- Then I should see a detailed log of all past maintenance activities, including dates, descriptions, and statuses.

#### Error Handling

- Given there is an issue loading the vehicle details
- When I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- Then I should see an error message indicating the problem and suggesting potential actions (e.g., retry, contact support)

#### Responsive Design

- Given I am viewing the detail vehicle view on different devices (e.g., desktop, tablet, mobile)
- When the page loads
- Then the vehicle details and maintenance schedule should be displayed in a user-friend format, adapting to the screen size
card.name: US-2 Acceptance Criteria: View Vehicle Details

  - Year
  - Status (e.g., available, in maintenance, in use)
  - Current location

#### Accurate Data Display

- Given there are vehicles in the fleet database
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then the displayed list should accurately reflect the current inventory and statuses of all vehicles in the fleet

#### Empty State Handling

- Given there are no vehicles in the fleet database
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then I should see a message indicating that no vehicles are currently available in the fleet.

#### Search

- Give I am viewing the “Vehicle List”
- When I use the search option
- Then the vehicle list should update to display only the vehicles that match the search criteria.

cards.desc:
## **User Story 1: View Vehicle List**

- As a fleet manager
- I want to view a list of vehicles currently in the fleet
- So that I can quickly see which vehicles are available and their statuses.

### **Acceptance Criteria**

#### **Display Vehicle List**

- Given I am on the homepage of the fleet management app
- When the page loads
- Then I should see a list of all vehicles in the fleet

#### Vehicle Details in List

- Given I am view the “Vehicle List”
- When the vehicle list is displayed
- Then I should see the following details
  - VIN (data-mask all but last 6 characters)
  - Make
  - Model
  - Year
  - Status (e.g., available, in maintenance, in use)
  - Current location

#### Accurate Data Display

- Given there are vehicles in the fleet database
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then the displayed list should accurately reflect the current inventory and statuses of all vehicles in the fleet

#### Empty State Handling

- Given there are no vehicles in the fleet database
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then I should see a message indicating that no vehicles are currently available in the fleet.

#### Search

- Given I am viewing the “Vehicle List”
- When I use the search option
- Then the vehicle list should update to display only the vehicles that match the search criteria.

#### Pagination

- Given there are more vehicles in the fleet than can be displayed on a single page
- When I view the “Vehicle List”
- Then the list should be paginated, and I should be able to navigate between pages
cards.name: US-1 Acceptance Criteria: View Vehicle List

cards.desc:
## User Story 2: View Vehicle Details

- As a fleet manager
- When I click on a vehicle in the list
- Then I should see its detailed specifications, including make, model, year, and maintenance schedule

### Acceptance Criteria

#### Clickable Vehicle Entries

- Given I am viewing the vehicle list
- When I click on a vehicle entry
- Then I should be navigated to a detailed view page for that vehicle

#### Display Vehicle Specifications

- Given I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- When the page loads
- Then I should see the vehicle’s specifications, including
  - Make
  - Model
  - Year
  - VIN (Vehicle Identification Number)
  - License Plate Number (if applicable)
  - Current Status

#### Display Maintenance Schedule

- Given I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- When the page loads
- Then I should see the vehicles maintenance schedule, including:
  - Upcoming maintenance tasks with due dates
  - Past maintenance history with completion dates
  - Current maintenance status (e.g., overdue, upcoming, completed)

#### Navigation to Maintenance History

- Given I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- When I click on a “View Maintenance History” link or button
- Then I should see a detailed log of all past maintenance activities, including dates, descriptions, and statuses.

#### Error Handling

- Given there is an issue loading the vehicle details
- When I am on the detailed view page for a vehicle
- Then I should see an error message indicating the problem and suggesting potential actions (e.g., retry, contact support)

#### Responsive Design

- Given I am viewing the detail vehicle view on different devices (e.g., desktop, tablet, mobile)
- When the page loads
- Then the vehicle details and maintenance schedule should be displayed in a user-friend format, adapting to the screen size
cards.name: US-2 Acceptance Criteria: View Vehicle Details

cards.desc:
DoD GOV fleet managers require a singular application that enables tracking the status of the organization’s current vehicle fleet, the ability to add or remove approved vehicles to said fleet, and those vehicles individual specifications and maintenance requirements.

‌

Stretch Goals:
\- Vehicle’s current location
\- Auction/Bidding page
\- Potential financial considerations
cards.name: Problem Statement w/ Stretch Goals

cards.desc:
User: Fleet manager/maintainer (additional duty holder)

‌

Home Page: shows current fleet + remove vehicle button

Details Page: vehicle specifications

EPL: shows approved vehicles + add vehicle button
cards.name: Determine MVP

cards.desc:
```
- **View Fleet:** Display a list of all vehicles in the fleet with essential details like year, make, model, and VIN.
- **Vehicle Details:** View detailed information about individual vehicles, including images, specifications, and maintenance requirements.
- **Maintenance Tracking:** Keep track of maintenance schedules and requirements for each vehicle.
- **Search and Filter:** Easily search and filter vehicles based on various criteria.
- **Car News:** Displays a list of links to news articles regarding vehicles.
```

checkItems.name: Should implement standard hooks such as useState, useEffect, and useContext.
Should recognize situations and implement custom hooks where they can provide dynamic reusable hooks for multiple components to utilize.
Should gracefully handle page refreshes on non-root routes.
Unit testing should be implemented for any functionality deemed critical to a component.
UI testing with should be implemented to ensure that the application as a whole behaves functionally as intended as well as behaving as expected for a potential user.

Feel free to use any styling libraries and/or philosophies that seems appropriate to your app, as long as your group stays consistent and you are able to achieve an effective implementation and appealing, visually cohesive final product.

You may utilize a library like styled-components or material-ui. If you'd like to make use of a different library or approach than those covered in the curriculum thus far, keep in mind that troubleshooting from instructors may be more limited depending on your choice.
No hard styling guides or requirements will be assessed, just ensure that the styling for each component matches well with the rest of the application.

Take a look at the Curated APIs List from Project 1. If none of the choices fit into the application you had in mind, feel free to create your own dummy data and use it as a replacement to data from an API. Just be careful not to fall down the rabbit hole of spending too much time crafting your dummy data.
Should implement at least 3 separate routes using React Router.
Should implement testing on all top-level components.
